The '''Association for the Study of Law, Culture and the Humanities''' is scholarly association for interdisciplinary research in the fields of law, culture, and the humanities.<ref name=Palgrave /> Since the inaugural event at [[Georgetown Law]] in 1998,<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=vjskDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT22|page=22|title=New Directions in Law and Literature |author=Elizabeth S. Anker |author2=Bernadette Meyler |publisher=Oxford University Press|date=2017}}</ref> the organization has held an annual conference hosted by a different law school each year,<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=GCpbdqaa1skC&pg=PA169 |page=169 |title=Cavendish: Jurisprudence Lawcards |publisher=Routledge |author=Psychology Press |date=2006}}</ref> and has published the journal ''[[Law, Culture and the Humanities]]'' since 2005.<ref name=Palgrave>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=tnAFCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA6 |page=6 |title=Hollywood and the Law |author=Paul McDonald |author2=Emily Carman |author3=Eric Hoyt |author4=Philip Drake |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |year=2015}}</ref>
