{{nihongo|'''''Cheating Craft'''''|チーティングクラフト|}} is a Japanese/Chinese [[Anime series|anime television series]] animated by BLADE and produced by [[Haoliners Animation League|Emon]]. It is based on Gemini Xin Luo's novel ''Zuobi Yishu'' (Chinese 作弊艺术). The anime series premiered on October 5, 2016 as a short anime and ran alongside ''[[To Be Hero]]''.<ref name="ANN 1">{{cite web|title=Emon Announces New Cheating Craft Anime for October 5|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-06/emon-announces-new-cheating-craft-anime-for-october-5/.106184|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=September 7, 2016|date=September 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Fall "Cheating Craft" Shorts To Adapt Chinese Novel|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/09/06-1/fall-cheating-craft-shorts-to-adapt-chinese-novel|website=Crunchyroll|accessdate=September 7, 2016|date=September 7, 2016}}</ref>

== Plot ==
In a world where people have been sorted since childhood by exams, only those who excel obtain happiness. L (Learning) Types, who prioritize study, and C (Cheating) Types, those who choose not to study to pass, will battle and team up in exams. C Type protagonist Muming Zhuge 诸葛睦明 (Japanese: Mumei Shokatsu) and L Type heroine Qiaoyi Huang 黄巧衣 (Japanese: Kōi Oh) battle together to pass tests.

